# PvP signaling broker (PeerJS). Copy to `.env` for local builds, and set the
# same vars in your front-end host's build environment for production.
#
# Leave ALL of these UNSET for plain `npm run dev` — the client falls back to
# the public PeerJS cloud broker, which is fine for quick local testing.
#
# Set VITE_PEER_HOST to your deployed broker (see render.yaml) to make
# matchmaking reliable across different networks.

# VITE_PEER_HOST=hook-trainer-peer.onrender.com
# VITE_PEER_PORT=443
# VITE_PEER_PATH=/myapp
# VITE_PEER_SECURE=true
